TI  - Effects of Post-Privatization Governance and Strategies on Export Intensity in the Former Soviet Union
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 853
EP  - 871
VL  - 32
IS  - 4
AB  - The fall of the Soviet Union brought new enterprise opportunities whose exploitation required the development of entirely new strategies. Simultaneously, enterprises faced crucial constraints in their governance structures. This paper analyzes the impact of governance structures of privatized firms on one key outcome of new strategies: export intensity. Using a longitudinal, multi-industry dataset of privatized firms in Russia, Ukraine and Belarus, we analyze how export intensity is mediated by strategies involving product development, acquisitions and links with foreign partners.
